1
00:00:03,503 --> 00:00:05,205
Will you be my wife?

2
00:00:06,406 --> 00:00:09,877
I'm quitting photography
to run my family's business.

3
00:00:11,912 --> 00:00:13,647
Come to Kanazawa with me.

4
00:00:14,915 --> 00:00:17,484
Take your time to think it over.

5
00:00:17,518 --> 00:00:18,418
Yes, I'd love to!

6
00:00:19,419 --> 00:00:21,355
- Really?
- Yeah.

7
00:00:21,688 --> 00:00:23,123
Right?

8
00:00:24,191 --> 00:00:24,758
Yes.

9
00:00:25,692 --> 00:00:29,162
All right!

10
00:00:31,665 --> 00:00:34,868
All milk ristretto shot...

11
00:00:34,902 --> 00:00:37,704
All milk ristretto shot non-syrup
soy latte. Tall.

12
00:00:38,238 --> 00:00:39,172
That's mine.

13
00:00:39,806 --> 00:00:41,074
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

14
00:00:42,209 --> 00:00:43,543
A hot cafe latte.

15
00:00:44,011 --> 00:00:45,145
Hello.

16
00:00:45,612 --> 00:00:47,180
- Good morning, Nami.
- Good morning.

17
00:00:47,214 --> 00:00:49,750
I'm taking
the 10 AM bullet train today.

18
00:00:50,017 --> 00:00:53,820
I have a meeting this evening.
I wish I could see you off, but...

19
00:00:54,154 --> 00:00:57,357
That's okay.
I'll be back the day after tomorrow.

20
00:00:57,858 --> 00:01:00,527
Let's have hot pot when I come back.

21
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:02,796
With soymilk. The creamy type.

22
00:01:04,431 --> 00:01:05,632
Take care.

23
00:01:05,999 --> 00:01:06,800
Bye.

24
00:01:07,901 --> 00:01:09,303
Mr. Jun?

25
00:01:09,336 --> 00:01:12,272
Is this all you're sending
to Kanazawa?

26
00:01:12,306 --> 00:01:13,473
Yeah, thanks.

27
00:01:15,242 --> 00:01:16,476
Thanks, got it.

28
00:01:18,512 --> 00:01:19,279
There.

29
00:01:21,515 --> 00:01:24,718
You're really leaving
for Kanazawa, huh?

30
00:01:25,586 --> 00:01:28,722
- Yeah.
- So is Nami quitting her job?

31
00:01:29,623 --> 00:01:32,326
Yeah, I'm not sure yet.

32
00:01:32,359 --> 00:01:33,560
What do you mean?

33
00:01:33,961 --> 00:01:38,198
I haven't asked her if
she wants to continue working.

34
00:01:38,231 --> 00:01:40,434
And if she has a goal now.

35
00:01:40,801 --> 00:01:43,937
I wanted to know,
and that's why I proposed to her.

36
00:01:43,971 --> 00:01:46,807
Gosh, you've really thought this over.

37
00:01:47,507 --> 00:01:48,909
You're so cool.

38
00:01:49,977 --> 00:01:50,877
Am I?

39
00:01:51,578 --> 00:01:52,679
Good morning...

40
00:01:55,248 --> 00:01:56,183
Huh?

41
00:01:56,216 --> 00:01:57,818
Everyone, gather around.

42
00:01:59,052 --> 00:02:03,790
The merger with First Publishing
will become official next month.

43
00:02:03,824 --> 00:02:07,961
This editing department will also
become a part of First Publishing.

44
00:02:07,995 --> 00:02:09,262
Yeah, we know that.

45
00:02:09,696 --> 00:02:11,832
Did I already tell you that? Right.

46
00:02:11,865 --> 00:02:14,768
- So, well, um...
- Get to the point.

47
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:15,836
Good morning.

48
00:02:15,869 --> 00:02:17,104
Good...

49
00:02:19,706 --> 00:02:20,841
Zeal's editor-in-chief.

50
00:02:21,108 --> 00:02:22,509
You finally remembered.

51
00:02:22,743 --> 00:02:24,077
But I'm not anymore.

52
00:02:25,278 --> 00:02:28,682
I'm the new editor-in-chief of Miyavi.

53
00:02:28,715 --> 00:02:31,718
My name is Asami Takahashi.
Nice to meet you.

54
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:35,088
What did you just say?

55
00:02:35,122 --> 00:02:36,056
Handa.

56
00:02:36,089 --> 00:02:40,193
Well you see, Boss...
I mean Ms. Horai.

57
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:42,295
She's no longer on this team.

58
00:02:43,897 --> 00:02:44,931
No way.

59
00:02:45,198 --> 00:02:47,467
Ms. Takahashi will be our new boss.

60
00:02:47,668 --> 00:02:48,702
Let's do it!

61
00:02:49,403 --> 00:02:50,337
Okay.

62
00:02:53,206 --> 00:02:54,074
Fine.

63
00:02:55,308 --> 00:02:58,712
Anyways, I'm going to change things up
for Miyavi.

64
00:02:59,479 --> 00:03:03,583
Starting with the next issue,
we'll have designer brand freebies.

65
00:03:04,051 --> 00:03:07,654
I need you all to come up
with freebie ideas by next meeting.

66
00:03:08,455 --> 00:03:09,289
Freebies.

67
00:03:09,589 --> 00:03:11,291
That's not Miyavi.

68
00:03:13,827 --> 00:03:15,962
Okay, Suzuki?

69
00:03:18,198 --> 00:03:19,132
Wake up.

70
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:24,171
My stuff will be here shortly.
Bring it up to my office.

71
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:29,743
What's going on, Mr. Handa?

72
00:03:30,310 --> 00:03:32,679
What's the use of continuing Miyavi
like this?

73
00:03:33,380 --> 00:03:35,282
Where's Ms. Horai?

74
00:03:35,315 --> 00:03:36,850
She's...

75
00:03:37,717 --> 00:03:38,585
She's missing.

76
00:03:42,456 --> 00:03:43,690
Missing?

77
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:50,931
Oh My Boss! Love Not Included

78
00:03:54,201 --> 00:03:55,402
Excuse me.

79
00:03:56,203 --> 00:03:58,705
- Suzuki?
- Mr. Handa?

80
00:04:04,077 --> 00:04:05,812
- What is it?
- Nothing.

81
00:04:07,481 --> 00:04:08,615
- What?
- Nothing.

82
00:04:09,649 --> 00:04:12,319
- What is it?
- Nothing, nothing.

83
00:04:12,686 --> 00:04:14,754
Nothing, nothing...

84
00:04:15,922 --> 00:04:17,124
Letter of resignation?

85
00:04:17,924 --> 00:04:18,825
What do you mean?

86
00:04:19,459 --> 00:04:21,394
I was just asking him the same thing.

87
00:04:22,529 --> 00:04:27,534
Ms. Horai left Miyavi
because of that tabloid article.

88
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:30,537
I believe I may have leaked
the information.

89
00:04:30,570 --> 00:04:34,107
I can't stay here. Goodbye.

90
00:04:34,574 --> 00:04:36,109
Hold on a second.

91
00:04:37,778 --> 00:04:40,413
There's no proof it leaked from you.

92
00:04:41,381 --> 00:04:43,083
There's no proof that it didn't.

93
00:04:44,684 --> 00:04:50,590
But without you,
we'd be even less like Miyavi.

94
00:04:50,891 --> 00:04:52,492
I'm honored you feel that way.

95
00:04:54,060 --> 00:04:55,095
Suzuki.

96
00:04:56,129 --> 00:04:57,464
Good luck.

97
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:00,800
I'm rooting for you.

98
00:05:03,537 --> 00:05:04,838
Mr. Handa...

99
00:05:09,376 --> 00:05:13,013
I begged him not to quit,

100
00:05:13,046 --> 00:05:17,484
but if I'm going to Kanazawa,
I'd have to quit too.

101
00:05:18,351 --> 00:05:20,353
Nice and relaxed, good.

102
00:05:21,254 --> 00:05:23,123
Okay, change the set.

103
00:05:24,324 --> 00:05:25,859
Suzuki, where are the props?

104
00:05:25,892 --> 00:05:27,360
Right here.

105
00:05:31,064 --> 00:05:32,833
- Here.
- Thanks.

106
00:05:34,401 --> 00:05:35,835
About this.

107
00:05:36,636 --> 00:05:40,874
Since pink is the concept
you're going with,

108
00:05:40,907 --> 00:05:43,009
I thought these might work too.

109
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:47,781
Good choice.

110
00:05:52,052 --> 00:05:53,553
Congrats.

111
00:05:54,221 --> 00:05:57,624
Bring in some extra props
next time, too.

112
00:06:06,132 --> 00:06:07,767
Come to Kanazawa with me.

113
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:12,839
You sure do love to daydream.

114
00:06:12,872 --> 00:06:13,974
Sorry.

115
00:06:16,676 --> 00:06:20,981
I was just thinking
how great this job is.

116
00:06:23,850 --> 00:06:25,752
I don't know how to put it.

117
00:06:26,453 --> 00:06:29,189
Is this what you call a dream?

118
00:06:29,456 --> 00:06:32,158
Don't fret over
whether or not it's your dream.

119
00:06:33,226 --> 00:06:35,595
Make it your dream,
and then start fretting.

120
00:06:36,796 --> 00:06:37,664
Right...

121
00:06:38,965 --> 00:06:42,135
You say such wise stuff.
You need to make a calendar.

122
00:06:42,335 --> 00:06:44,571
Whatever, shut up.

123
00:06:45,639 --> 00:06:47,407
Suzuki.

124
00:06:47,440 --> 00:06:50,844
Remember how I said if you're
just here until you get married,

125
00:06:50,877 --> 00:06:53,246
you should find an easier job?

126
00:06:54,147 --> 00:06:55,315
Did you?

127
00:06:55,815 --> 00:06:58,118
Yeah, I sure did.

128
00:06:58,852 --> 00:07:01,721
You've changed since then.

129
00:07:02,555 --> 00:07:03,757
Have I?

130
00:07:10,263 --> 00:07:11,798
You're quite the rival now.

131
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:16,169
Izumi, Nakazawa, help me out.

132
00:07:19,606 --> 00:07:21,241
"You're quite the rival now."

133
00:07:24,978 --> 00:07:26,046
Thank you for this food.

134
00:07:31,151 --> 00:07:33,219
- Hello?
- Nami?

135
00:07:33,453 --> 00:07:34,954
What is it?

136
00:07:35,488 --> 00:07:36,690
I wanted to hear your voice.

137
00:07:37,724 --> 00:07:38,925
Here I am.

138
00:07:39,392 --> 00:07:41,461
I told my parents about you.

139
00:07:41,728 --> 00:07:43,430
They're really happy.

140
00:07:43,963 --> 00:07:48,101
Mom asks me every day
what kind of girl you are.

141
00:07:48,568 --> 00:07:49,903
What do you tell her?

142
00:07:49,936 --> 00:07:53,006
That you're this tall,
have this long hair.

143
00:07:54,574 --> 00:07:56,810
I don't think that's what she means.

144
00:07:56,843 --> 00:08:00,246
They asked if you'd like to
have dinner in Tokyo this weekend.

145
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:01,781
Well, sure.

146
00:08:02,549 --> 00:08:03,483
But I'm so nervous.

147
00:08:04,184 --> 00:08:05,418
I'll make reservations.

148
00:08:05,452 --> 00:08:09,589
Does that mean Ms. Horai will come?

149
00:08:09,622 --> 00:08:10,290
What, Sis?

150
00:08:10,323 --> 00:08:13,460
You see, she quit Miyavi.

151
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:15,328
We can't reach her.

152
00:08:16,396 --> 00:08:19,332
That's it? Aren't you worried?

153
00:08:19,366 --> 00:08:21,668
She always makes her own choices.

154
00:08:21,968 --> 00:08:23,103
I see.

155
00:08:23,970 --> 00:08:27,140
But will you let me know
if she contacts you?

156
00:08:27,741 --> 00:08:28,541
Sure.

157
00:08:28,575 --> 00:08:29,809
Thanks.

158
00:08:29,843 --> 00:08:32,345
I'll let you know about dinner.

159
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:43,123
Traditional Crafts

160
00:08:45,792 --> 00:08:47,961
Traditional Crafts

161
00:08:48,728 --> 00:08:51,831
Photography by Junnosuke Horai

162
00:08:53,466 --> 00:08:54,534
Mr. Horai.

163
00:08:55,035 --> 00:08:56,169
You must be Mr. Horai.

164
00:08:56,903 --> 00:08:59,005
Nice to meet you. I'm Junnosuke Horai.

165
00:08:59,038 --> 00:09:03,476
Sorry for making you wait.
You must be so busy.

166
00:09:03,510 --> 00:09:04,711
Not at all.

167
00:09:06,079 --> 00:09:07,580
About this picture.

168
00:09:07,614 --> 00:09:11,217
That old thing?
We're going to change it soon.

169
00:09:12,185 --> 00:09:17,190
Anyways, we are ever so grateful
for your father.

170
00:09:17,924 --> 00:09:19,192
I hope he is well?

171
00:09:20,393 --> 00:09:21,694
Thank you for this food.

172
00:09:23,930 --> 00:09:24,998
Ms. Suzuki.

173
00:09:25,632 --> 00:09:26,566
Mr. Ugajin.

174
00:09:27,700 --> 00:09:28,735
Oh, Mr. Ugajin!

175
00:09:30,370 --> 00:09:31,671
I need to ask you something.

176
00:09:31,704 --> 00:09:33,206
I can't tell you.

177
00:09:33,506 --> 00:09:35,341
You mean, you know where she is?

178
00:09:35,775 --> 00:09:38,011
She told me not to tell anyone.

179
00:09:40,847 --> 00:09:43,383
She could've said goodbye.

180
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:48,154
With this merger...

181
00:09:49,155 --> 00:09:51,458
the original plan was to fire you.

182
00:09:53,793 --> 00:09:59,065
Without the editor-in-chief,
why leave her assistant, right?

183
00:10:00,066 --> 00:10:04,737
But your boss asked me not to do that.

184
00:10:05,371 --> 00:10:08,141
Ms. Horai did?

185
00:10:08,408 --> 00:10:13,113
Novels and non-fiction books
can be published with just one editor.

186
00:10:13,980 --> 00:10:15,982
But magazines can't be made alone.

187
00:10:16,816 --> 00:10:20,420
So it's important
to train new editors.

188
00:10:22,222 --> 00:10:25,592
Money isn't the only thing we need
to recover as a publisher.

189
00:10:25,825 --> 00:10:27,560
What's important is the personnel.

190
00:10:28,161 --> 00:10:33,399
I believe that's why Ms. Horai
told me not to fire you.

191
00:10:35,301 --> 00:10:39,873
Even though Otowado is no longer.

192
00:10:43,610 --> 00:10:45,512
Oh yeah.

193
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:50,483
How are things with her?

194
00:10:51,351 --> 00:10:52,252
I think...

195
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:55,054
She turned me down.

196
00:10:56,422 --> 00:10:57,223
Ms. Reiko!

197
00:11:00,493 --> 00:11:01,394
Mr. Ugajin.

198
00:11:04,197 --> 00:11:06,499
There's no reason for you to quit.

199
00:11:07,166 --> 00:11:09,068
- I'll talk to...
- Mr. Ugajin.

200
00:11:09,969 --> 00:11:14,307
My role here
was to prevent the merger.

201
00:11:15,241 --> 00:11:16,543
Let me take responsibility.

202
00:11:16,576 --> 00:11:18,511
- But Ms. Reiko...
- The aquarium.

203
00:11:19,646 --> 00:11:20,914
I had fun.

204
00:11:24,684 --> 00:11:26,352
I'll remember it forever.

205
00:11:28,288 --> 00:11:29,522
Thank you.

206
00:11:33,793 --> 00:11:39,265
Do you think maybe
I was too old for her?

207
00:11:43,903 --> 00:11:45,638
Chinese cabbage.

208
00:11:48,408 --> 00:11:50,176
- Rio.
- Jun!

209
00:11:51,177 --> 00:11:53,613
Wow, looking sharp.

210
00:11:55,615 --> 00:11:57,984
Having hot pot with Nami tonight?

211
00:11:59,285 --> 00:12:02,355
So things are going well, huh?

212
00:12:03,056 --> 00:12:04,290
Good for you.

213
00:12:07,827 --> 00:12:10,863
Are you guys getting married?

214
00:12:11,397 --> 00:12:13,333
I proposed to her.

215
00:12:15,468 --> 00:12:17,637
Way to go!

216
00:12:19,339 --> 00:12:20,540
Congratulations.

217
00:12:20,873 --> 00:12:21,774
Thanks.

218
00:12:22,775 --> 00:12:23,676
Wow.

219
00:12:26,245 --> 00:12:27,046
Yeah.

220
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:31,584
Hey, Jun?

221
00:12:32,285 --> 00:12:34,187
Before you get married...

222
00:12:35,188 --> 00:12:39,659
Can I ask you one last favor
as a childhood friend?

223
00:12:42,161 --> 00:12:43,863
I have an operation coming up.

224
00:12:44,797 --> 00:12:48,501
What do you mean?
You said it was an inflamed tendon.

225
00:12:50,236 --> 00:12:51,404
Sorry.

226
00:12:55,108 --> 00:12:57,243
Yummy.

227
00:13:02,715 --> 00:13:05,885
By the way.
I met Rio at the supermarket.

228
00:13:07,854 --> 00:13:09,022
Ms. Rio?

229
00:13:09,489 --> 00:13:11,491
She asked me to be there
for her surgery.

230
00:13:11,524 --> 00:13:12,592
Surgery?

231
00:13:14,494 --> 00:13:16,129
It's her hand.

232
00:13:18,464 --> 00:13:22,435
But I won't go
if you don't want me to.

233
00:13:23,269 --> 00:13:24,871
I can trust him, can't I?

234
00:13:25,438 --> 00:13:27,707
He said he only has eyes for me.

235
00:13:28,574 --> 00:13:29,642
But...

236
00:13:31,744 --> 00:13:33,346
Come here, Jun!

237
00:13:33,746 --> 00:13:36,816
Which is it, White Jun? Black Jun?

238
00:13:37,116 --> 00:13:39,352
Look that way!

239
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:49,328
It's White and Black Jun.

240
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:56,035
Arf. Rio.

241
00:13:57,236 --> 00:13:58,571
Arf. Nami!

242
00:14:00,907 --> 00:14:05,011
- Rio.
- No, don't! It's Nami!

243
00:14:08,448 --> 00:14:10,516
I mean, nothing.

244
00:14:13,086 --> 00:14:14,120
Should I say no?

245
00:14:16,889 --> 00:14:18,057
Of course not.

246
00:14:20,026 --> 00:14:20,793
Thanks.

247
00:14:22,128 --> 00:14:22,895
It's okay.

248
00:14:28,835 --> 00:14:31,704
Suzuki, aren't the sketchbooks
here yet?

249
00:14:31,738 --> 00:14:34,674
Sorry, they're here.
I forgot to put them away.

250
00:14:40,179 --> 00:14:42,915
- Sorry.
- Be sure to organize it.

251
00:14:42,949 --> 00:14:43,816
I will.

252
00:14:53,192 --> 00:14:54,761
Delivery receipt

253
00:14:56,996 --> 00:14:58,197
This...

254
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:06,873
Office Equipment Department

255
00:15:07,874 --> 00:15:08,808
Please.

256
00:15:12,912 --> 00:15:14,781
Horai

257
00:15:19,452 --> 00:15:20,286
Excuse me.

258
00:15:23,623 --> 00:15:25,124
Excuse me.

259
00:15:25,158 --> 00:15:26,993
Is this "Horai" person here?

260
00:15:28,761 --> 00:15:30,296
Yes, she's right there.

261
00:15:32,632 --> 00:15:33,866
Ms. Horai?

262
00:15:35,001 --> 00:15:36,969
I was looking everywhere for you!

263
00:15:37,336 --> 00:15:40,373
Ms. Horai, the staplers...?

264
00:15:40,406 --> 00:15:42,775
Third row deep, bottom right corner.

265
00:15:42,809 --> 00:15:44,911
Third row deep, bottom right, got it.

266
00:15:46,312 --> 00:15:49,048
- Um...
- Work hours. Wait till break time.

267
00:15:51,384 --> 00:15:53,019
- Goodnight.
- Goodnight.

268
00:15:53,786 --> 00:15:56,823
Ms. Horai, please come back to Miyavi.

269
00:15:57,557 --> 00:16:00,326
She's turning Miyavi
into a whole different magazine.

270
00:16:01,694 --> 00:16:03,996
Why are you in Equipment Management?

271
00:16:04,263 --> 00:16:05,698
Why should I answer you?

272
00:16:05,865 --> 00:16:07,266
Come on.

273
00:16:08,901 --> 00:16:14,307
Mr. Handa turned in his resignation
because he felt responsible for you.

274
00:16:15,675 --> 00:16:18,945
I was asked to join the company
to prevent the merger.

275
00:16:19,879 --> 00:16:21,314
But I couldn't.

276
00:16:23,382 --> 00:16:28,454
So I requested to come here
to be of any help to the company.

277
00:16:29,589 --> 00:16:32,692
Mr. Handa doesn't have to quit.
Tell him that.

278
00:16:33,392 --> 00:16:34,393
Okay.

279
00:16:35,194 --> 00:16:36,028
But...

280
00:16:38,331 --> 00:16:39,632
My break is over.

281
00:16:41,734 --> 00:16:42,935
I...

282
00:16:46,405 --> 00:16:49,175
Junnosuke proposed to me.

283
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:51,811
I said yes.

284
00:16:52,545 --> 00:16:54,080
So you're quitting?

285
00:16:55,781 --> 00:16:58,451
To be honest,
I hadn't thought it over.

286
00:17:00,219 --> 00:17:03,122
Do you know why I kept you
from being fired?

287
00:17:31,918 --> 00:17:32,985
So cute.

288
00:17:37,490 --> 00:17:38,758
You scared me.

289
00:17:39,892 --> 00:17:41,193
You were awake?

290
00:18:15,428 --> 00:18:16,362
Goodnight.

291
00:18:17,196 --> 00:18:18,097
Goodnight.

292
00:18:27,740 --> 00:18:29,075
What's the meaning of this?

293
00:18:29,408 --> 00:18:32,311
I told you to brainstorm
freebie ideas.

294
00:18:34,146 --> 00:18:37,316
"Energetic mode, my favorite items."

295
00:18:37,883 --> 00:18:40,686
"Let's shine brighter,
the power of fashion."

296
00:18:41,187 --> 00:18:44,657
All stuff Reiko would've liked.

297
00:18:46,492 --> 00:18:51,931
Miyavi has always been driven
by the contents.

298
00:18:51,964 --> 00:18:52,965
The contents?

299
00:18:54,734 --> 00:18:55,635
You all think so?

300
00:18:57,570 --> 00:18:58,537
Well.

301
00:19:00,006 --> 00:19:01,440
We're running a business.

302
00:19:01,741 --> 00:19:05,544
What happens to publishers
who prints magazines that don't sell?

303
00:19:05,578 --> 00:19:07,380
You all know very well, don't you?

304
00:19:09,382 --> 00:19:11,684
That's enough for today.

305
00:19:12,451 --> 00:19:15,921
Congratulations on becoming
Miyavi's new editor-in-chief.

306
00:19:15,955 --> 00:19:17,189
Thank you.

307
00:19:17,723 --> 00:19:21,027
I believe I may have been able
to aid you a little.

308
00:19:23,996 --> 00:19:26,632
That tabloid article about Ms. Horai.

309
00:19:26,966 --> 00:19:29,335
I leaked it.

310
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:38,077
I thought she was a bit smarter.

311
00:19:38,110 --> 00:19:40,212
If she'd joined hands with me...

312
00:19:43,916 --> 00:19:49,488
Unfortunately, the new editor-in-chief
isn't so smart either.

313
00:19:49,789 --> 00:19:50,623
Good day.

314
00:19:59,398 --> 00:20:01,300
Dang, she was my type.

315
00:20:01,333 --> 00:20:01,634
Operation Bring Back Ms. Horai

316
00:20:01,634 --> 00:20:03,569
Let's make her come back.

317
00:20:03,602 --> 00:20:04,804
We need a plan!

318
00:20:04,937 --> 00:20:08,207
According to Suzuki,
Ms. Horai is in the Equipment Dept.

319
00:20:08,240 --> 00:20:11,377
She's like their savior now, right?

320
00:20:12,378 --> 00:20:16,048
You know her the best.
How do we get to her?

321
00:20:16,549 --> 00:20:18,117
Let me think.

322
00:20:22,521 --> 00:20:24,490
I have an idea.

323
00:20:24,890 --> 00:20:28,894
What we need to do
is to just be totally honest.

324
00:20:28,928 --> 00:20:30,329
We'll give it our best shot.

325
00:20:31,363 --> 00:20:32,131
Go for it.

326
00:20:36,702 --> 00:20:40,072
Ms. Horai,
we may have rebelled at first.

327
00:20:40,106 --> 00:20:42,341
- But now...
- Your orders are here.

328
00:20:43,142 --> 00:20:44,110
Thank you.

329
00:20:54,753 --> 00:20:56,622
Any other plans?

330
00:21:00,559 --> 00:21:03,262
There was just one thing
Ms. Horai reacted to.

331
00:21:03,996 --> 00:21:05,498
What is it? Tell us?

332
00:21:07,533 --> 00:21:11,036
Where's Mr. Handa right now?

333
00:21:15,074 --> 00:21:18,344
Mr. Handa, what do you mean
you're quitting?

334
00:21:18,377 --> 00:21:19,712
Please take it back!

335
00:21:19,745 --> 00:21:20,846
Don't quit!

336
00:21:21,180 --> 00:21:23,949
Please, Mr. Handa.

337
00:21:25,417 --> 00:21:28,554
Suzuki, I told you
not to tell anybody.

338
00:21:28,988 --> 00:21:31,991
But we don't want you to quit!

339
00:21:32,758 --> 00:21:33,659
Please come back!

340
00:21:34,326 --> 00:21:36,695
But what I have done...

341
00:21:40,766 --> 00:21:43,602
- Sorry, one sec.
- Huh?

342
00:21:43,636 --> 00:21:45,738
Ms. Takahashi? Yes?

343
00:21:47,239 --> 00:21:50,743
I wasn't the one
that leaked to the tabloid?

344
00:21:51,377 --> 00:21:54,280
I'm innocent? I don't have to quit?

345
00:21:54,613 --> 00:21:55,814
Thank you!

346
00:22:02,121 --> 00:22:04,890
We're still together!

347
00:22:04,957 --> 00:22:06,058
Quit already.

348
00:22:53,505 --> 00:22:54,340
Who?

349
00:22:56,475 --> 00:22:59,278
Scram! Stay away from me!

350
00:23:00,279 --> 00:23:03,315
No, please.

351
00:23:03,349 --> 00:23:05,885
- I'm not...
- Who are you?

352
00:23:06,485 --> 00:23:08,187
I'm so sorry.

353
00:23:09,188 --> 00:23:11,624
I had no idea
you were Junnosuke's mother.

354
00:23:12,091 --> 00:23:15,394
Not at all, I'm the one
that needs to apologize.

355
00:23:15,427 --> 00:23:18,497
I was just curious about
what his girlfriend was like.

356
00:23:19,098 --> 00:23:21,867
I couldn't wait for our dinner.

357
00:23:22,735 --> 00:23:25,170
You're Reiko's assistant too, right?

358
00:23:26,305 --> 00:23:27,640
Well, my boss...

359
00:23:28,841 --> 00:23:32,945
Will Ms. Reiko come to the dinner?

360
00:23:32,978 --> 00:23:36,181
We invited her,
but she probably won't come.

361
00:23:37,716 --> 00:23:43,022
She and her father haven't been
on good terms for a long time.

362
00:23:43,055 --> 00:23:44,423
Let me know when
you decide on an apartment.

363
00:23:44,423 --> 00:23:47,760
12 years ago

364
00:23:48,494 --> 00:23:49,628
Okay. I'm going now.

365
00:23:52,464 --> 00:23:53,699
Bye, Dad.

366
00:24:01,740 --> 00:24:03,042
I'm sorry, Dad.

367
00:24:04,410 --> 00:24:07,179
I'm going to study fashion
for two years now.

368
00:24:08,180 --> 00:24:12,618
I want to find out what I'm good at
and what I want to do.

369
00:24:12,785 --> 00:24:13,919
What a waste.

370
00:24:15,554 --> 00:24:17,690
You could be wasting two whole years.

371
00:24:20,192 --> 00:24:22,027
Even if it doesn't work out...

372
00:24:23,896 --> 00:24:25,698
- It's not a waste.
- Enough.

373
00:24:26,465 --> 00:24:28,634
I'm giving Horai Paperworks
to Junnosuke.

374
00:24:31,003 --> 00:24:31,870
End of conversation.

375
00:24:32,271 --> 00:24:33,939
And that was the end of that.

376
00:24:34,506 --> 00:24:37,976
Reiko had always strived so hard
since she was a child

377
00:24:37,976 --> 00:24:42,314
to make her father happy.

378
00:24:42,681 --> 00:24:46,085
Her father had
such high hopes for her.

379
00:24:46,585 --> 00:24:48,921
Maybe that's what the problem was.

380
00:24:52,291 --> 00:24:53,926
You see, our family...

381
00:24:54,259 --> 00:24:57,463
It's a little special.

382
00:24:57,863 --> 00:25:02,368
Please, take your time to adjust.

383
00:25:04,503 --> 00:25:05,270
Yes.

384
00:25:07,406 --> 00:25:09,775
Would you say you look
more like your mother?

385
00:25:11,677 --> 00:25:13,779
Yeah, I guess so.

386
00:25:13,812 --> 00:25:14,947
I thought so too.

387
00:25:14,980 --> 00:25:17,082
Warm and kind.

388
00:25:19,585 --> 00:25:23,188
Ms. Horai is more like
your father, huh?

389
00:25:24,890 --> 00:25:27,659
Yeah, they've got
the same personalities.

390
00:25:28,060 --> 00:25:29,428
They're both perfectionists.

391
00:25:38,270 --> 00:25:41,006
- What is it?
- Just looking for something.

392
00:25:42,741 --> 00:25:45,010
Otowado House Journal

393
00:25:53,051 --> 00:25:54,253
You again.

394
00:26:00,692 --> 00:26:04,730
Even if it doesn't work out,
it's not a waste, right?

395
00:26:09,334 --> 00:26:11,069
Dinner will be here tonight.

396
00:26:48,574 --> 00:26:49,341
Nami.

397
00:26:49,675 --> 00:26:51,076
You like it?

398
00:26:51,777 --> 00:26:52,744
It's delicious.

399
00:26:54,880 --> 00:26:56,515
What a perfect match for you.

400
00:26:57,649 --> 00:26:59,718
Can't wait for a baby.

401
00:26:59,751 --> 00:27:00,752
Baby?

402
00:27:00,786 --> 00:27:02,287
Calm down, jeez.

403
00:27:02,321 --> 00:27:03,555
Why not?

404
00:27:03,789 --> 00:27:07,559
You must come to Kanazawa soon.
Shall I book a wedding venue?

405
00:27:07,860 --> 00:27:09,862
That's quite sudden.

406
00:27:10,329 --> 00:27:12,064
I'm still working and...

407
00:27:12,564 --> 00:27:14,833
You're just working for Reiko, right?

408
00:27:15,067 --> 00:27:16,568
She'll cover for you.

409
00:27:17,069 --> 00:27:19,805
Well, about that.

410
00:27:21,874 --> 00:27:23,775
She quit the editing department.

411
00:27:24,309 --> 00:27:27,045
- Why?
- Mergers and stuff.

412
00:27:27,079 --> 00:27:30,315
That's why I introduced
Shintani to her.

413
00:27:30,649 --> 00:27:32,184
She shouldn't have resisted.

414
00:27:35,220 --> 00:27:35,988
Um...

415
00:27:36,755 --> 00:27:38,090
Will you look at this please?

416
00:27:41,093 --> 00:27:43,095
It's our house journal.

417
00:27:44,229 --> 00:27:46,732
It's the first article I ever made.

418
00:27:49,668 --> 00:27:52,204
I brought it because
I wanted you to see it.

419
00:27:56,675 --> 00:27:59,278
She's a really amazing person.

420
00:28:03,982 --> 00:28:07,019
"Reiko Horai's Killer Phrases"?

421
00:28:07,553 --> 00:28:08,153
If you can't get results,
I don't need you

422
00:28:08,153 --> 00:28:09,721
She's so passionate
about creating a good magazine.

423
00:28:09,721 --> 00:28:11,590
You may only speak
when I ask you a question

424
00:28:12,357 --> 00:28:14,192
She can do anything.

425
00:28:20,766 --> 00:28:23,435
And here.

426
00:28:24,036 --> 00:28:26,038
These are the issues she made.

427
00:28:27,372 --> 00:28:30,175
People all over the world read it.

428
00:28:30,409 --> 00:28:34,446
People we've never met before
turn its pages.

429
00:28:34,479 --> 00:28:36,782
They're excited by the new looks.

430
00:28:37,115 --> 00:28:38,584
Isn't that incredible?

431
00:28:39,718 --> 00:28:41,520
Ms. Horai...

432
00:28:41,553 --> 00:28:46,058
She taught me how wonderful
creating a magazine was.

433
00:28:48,393 --> 00:28:50,329
So, um...

434
00:28:52,564 --> 00:28:56,435
She's a really incredible person.

435
00:29:05,210 --> 00:29:11,083
Maybe there's more to her now
than what we thought we knew.

436
00:29:21,693 --> 00:29:23,662
I'm not incredible or anything.

437
00:29:27,666 --> 00:29:29,134
Reiko.

438
00:29:31,303 --> 00:29:32,471
Ms. Horai.

439
00:29:33,238 --> 00:29:34,806
Ten years ago...

440
00:29:36,008 --> 00:29:38,076
I read fashion magazines,
and I dreamed.

441
00:29:38,877 --> 00:29:44,483
I wanted to make a magazine
that would make such girls happy.

442
00:29:45,951 --> 00:29:47,919
And did what I had to do.

443
00:29:59,798 --> 00:30:04,536
Making magazines
are pretty amazing, huh.

444
00:30:18,950 --> 00:30:19,851
Reiko.

445
00:30:22,220 --> 00:30:23,121
I...

446
00:30:26,024 --> 00:30:27,059
I'm sorry.

447
00:30:29,795 --> 00:30:30,696
Forgive me.

448
00:30:44,076 --> 00:30:45,143
I'm sorry, too.

449
00:30:47,079 --> 00:30:48,714
For not running Horai Paperworks.

450
00:30:51,817 --> 00:30:56,021
And not making your dream come true.

451
00:31:01,359 --> 00:31:02,260
I'm sorry.

452
00:31:04,362 --> 00:31:08,533
As long as you're healthy and happy.

453
00:31:09,401 --> 00:31:10,469
I wish for nothing more.

454
00:31:25,484 --> 00:31:26,251
Ms. Horai.

455
00:31:30,021 --> 00:31:33,458
Won't you come back to Miyavi?

456
00:31:35,327 --> 00:31:39,164
There were so many things
I still wanted to learn from you.

457
00:31:42,300 --> 00:31:43,635
I think maybe...

458
00:31:46,404 --> 00:31:49,007
I might've discovered my dream.

459
00:31:49,541 --> 00:31:50,642
There's your answer.

460
00:31:57,115 --> 00:31:59,718
The reason I kept you
from being fired.

461
00:32:03,088 --> 00:32:04,222
Thank you for today.

462
00:32:41,693 --> 00:32:43,061
Junnosuke.

463
00:32:45,030 --> 00:32:46,064
What is it?

464
00:32:47,599 --> 00:32:48,500
Let's sit.

465
00:32:57,442 --> 00:33:00,412
We first met here, huh?

466
00:33:02,414 --> 00:33:05,450
It was wet with paint,
but you sat on it.

467
00:33:05,483 --> 00:33:07,886
And got paint on my butt.

468
00:33:07,919 --> 00:33:10,188
We ran to a shop to buy clothes.

469
00:33:10,222 --> 00:33:12,357
And you chose an outfit for me.

470
00:33:14,159 --> 00:33:15,560
Got your lucky charm?

471
00:33:15,927 --> 00:33:18,763
Of course. Got it right here.

472
00:33:24,102 --> 00:33:25,070
Then here.

473
00:33:26,304 --> 00:33:31,409
This is a token that means
you can trust me no matter what.

474
00:34:19,424 --> 00:34:20,492
Thank you.

475
00:34:31,102 --> 00:34:31,970
Nami.

476
00:34:35,740 --> 00:34:37,943
If you feel unsure about anything,

477
00:34:38,944 --> 00:34:40,178
I want you to tell me.

478
00:34:43,581 --> 00:34:46,084
I'm okay, right?

479
00:34:54,092 --> 00:34:55,060
I'm okay.

480
00:35:01,132 --> 00:35:02,133
Oh yeah.

481
00:35:02,634 --> 00:35:05,470
Let's go see those stars tonight.

482
00:35:06,304 --> 00:35:09,541
You can see lots of stars
up on our Tokyo branch building.

483
00:35:23,421 --> 00:35:25,957
Sorry for showing up all of a sudden.

484
00:35:27,258 --> 00:35:28,259
Thanks.

485
00:35:28,593 --> 00:35:32,163
I had to come say thank you.

486
00:35:34,766 --> 00:35:38,536
For letting Jun come with me
to my operation.

487
00:35:38,803 --> 00:35:39,871
Thank you.

488
00:35:39,904 --> 00:35:41,206
Not at all.

489
00:35:41,606 --> 00:35:44,009
I had no idea about your hand.

490
00:35:45,010 --> 00:35:46,311
I'm such a bad person.

491
00:35:47,545 --> 00:35:50,115
I always take advantage
of Jun's kindness.

492
00:35:53,652 --> 00:35:56,021
How's work going?

493
00:35:58,356 --> 00:35:59,591
At first...

494
00:36:01,059 --> 00:36:06,131
All I wanted was to have an average
marriage and live a stable life.

495
00:36:06,364 --> 00:36:08,667
That's what I came to Tokyo for.

496
00:36:11,202 --> 00:36:12,303
But now...

497
00:36:13,972 --> 00:36:16,541
I'm realizing how fun my job is.

498
00:36:17,942 --> 00:36:19,644
If I quit now...

499
00:36:20,745 --> 00:36:24,416
I'd feel like
I haven't accomplished anything.

500
00:36:25,984 --> 00:36:26,885
Yeah.

501
00:36:29,654 --> 00:36:33,558
Maybe becoming an editor
has become your dream.

502
00:36:35,160 --> 00:36:35,994
My dream?

503
00:36:40,865 --> 00:36:41,699
Yes...

504
00:36:44,069 --> 00:36:45,737
Maybe you're right.

505
00:36:48,540 --> 00:36:49,808
Welcome.

506
00:36:56,281 --> 00:36:59,284
- Soy sauce ramen, please.
- Coming right up.

507
00:36:59,317 --> 00:37:00,585
Welcome.

508
00:37:03,321 --> 00:37:05,457
- Miso ramen.
- One miso ramen.

509
00:37:05,490 --> 00:37:06,858
Mean senpai.

510
00:37:08,359 --> 00:37:09,127
You like miso?

511
00:37:10,628 --> 00:37:13,131
- Yeah.
- Oh.

512
00:37:14,199 --> 00:37:15,266
Nami.

513
00:37:16,401 --> 00:37:17,602
Sometimes,

514
00:37:17,769 --> 00:37:22,474
I feel like Jun is brushing aside
his own dreams.

515
00:37:23,074 --> 00:37:25,343
His own dreams?

516
00:37:27,345 --> 00:37:30,215
Because he has to run
the family business.

517
00:37:31,249 --> 00:37:34,219
Are dreams really that important?

518
00:37:36,087 --> 00:37:40,125
People can be held back
and bound down by their dreams.

519
00:37:40,759 --> 00:37:42,861
What's the use
if dreams keep you from smiling?

520
00:37:47,298 --> 00:37:48,266
If...

521
00:37:49,434 --> 00:37:51,870
If you're brushing aside
your dreams too,

522
00:37:52,537 --> 00:37:55,006
I think it'll sadden him.

523
00:37:56,708 --> 00:37:57,642
Nami.

524
00:37:58,510 --> 00:38:00,378
If you feel unsure about anything,

525
00:38:01,646 --> 00:38:02,747
I want you to tell me.

526
00:38:06,084 --> 00:38:07,585
I'm going to be blunt.

527
00:38:11,756 --> 00:38:15,226
If you feel you might regret
quitting your job and your dream,

528
00:38:16,995 --> 00:38:19,764
if you feel like
you'd be abandoning them,

529
00:38:21,933 --> 00:38:24,035
you'll just hurt him more.

530
00:38:28,673 --> 00:38:30,575
He's really kindhearted.

531
00:38:32,243 --> 00:38:33,244
That Jun.

532
00:38:46,140 --> 00:38:48,743
I proposed to Nami.

533
00:38:54,732 --> 00:38:57,435
So that's why she's talking about
dreams and stuff.

534
00:38:58,002 --> 00:39:00,504
I was just thinking
how great this job is.

535
00:39:01,105 --> 00:39:05,176
Is this what you call a dream?

536
00:39:07,044 --> 00:39:08,946
Marriage, huh?

537
00:39:11,048 --> 00:39:14,652
Suzuki is wanting to become an editor.

538
00:39:17,588 --> 00:39:18,422
I think.

539
00:39:19,190 --> 00:39:22,092
She's just discovering
how fun the job is.

540
00:39:27,198 --> 00:39:30,000
I know that, mean senpai.

541
00:39:33,137 --> 00:39:34,205
Yeah.

542
00:39:52,389 --> 00:39:56,260
If you feel like
you'd be abandoning them,

543
00:39:56,293 --> 00:39:58,662
you'll just hurt him more.

544
00:40:01,832 --> 00:40:02,800
Nami.

545
00:40:04,134 --> 00:40:04,902
I'm here.

546
00:40:12,977 --> 00:40:14,078
Wow.

547
00:40:15,379 --> 00:40:17,581
All these stars, here in the city.

548
00:40:18,716 --> 00:40:19,650
Amazing.

549
00:40:23,854 --> 00:40:24,688
It's cold.

550
00:40:33,697 --> 00:40:34,665
Warm now?

551
00:40:39,603 --> 00:40:40,905
So am I.

552
00:40:45,342 --> 00:40:46,544
Junnosuke.

553
00:40:54,485 --> 00:40:57,488
How I met you on that bench.

554
00:41:03,794 --> 00:41:05,663
And fell in love with you.

555
00:41:07,698 --> 00:41:10,234
And got to spend
all this time with you.

556
00:41:12,670 --> 00:41:15,072
I'm so lucky that I did.

557
00:41:21,779 --> 00:41:25,516
Let me guess. You found your dream?

558
00:41:58,749 --> 00:41:59,783
Don't cry.

559
00:42:04,054 --> 00:42:05,055
I...

560
00:42:07,925 --> 00:42:08,959
I...

561
00:42:09,526 --> 00:42:11,228
With you, I...

562
00:42:18,569 --> 00:42:19,570
I know.

563
00:42:29,246 --> 00:42:30,514
Nami.

564
00:42:32,883 --> 00:42:34,818
I want you to keep smiling.

565
00:42:52,236 --> 00:42:53,537
Junnosuke.

566
00:43:41,085 --> 00:43:41,885
Nami.

567
00:43:47,157 --> 00:43:48,358
Stay well.

568
00:43:52,996 --> 00:43:53,831
Yes.

569
00:45:02,533 --> 00:45:03,433
Saved.

570
00:45:05,602 --> 00:45:06,637
It's...

571
00:45:10,574 --> 00:45:14,278
It's raining.
We can't see the stars tonight.

572
00:45:14,311 --> 00:45:16,680
I love you, Nami.

573
00:45:18,582 --> 00:45:19,683
Recharging.

574
00:45:24,354 --> 00:45:25,923
This is my girlfriend.

575
00:45:26,323 --> 00:45:27,458
We're dating.

576
00:45:28,091 --> 00:45:29,493
Let's stay together forever.

577
00:45:29,726 --> 00:45:31,562
I only have eyes for you.

578
00:45:32,162 --> 00:45:33,931
Will you be my wife?

579
00:45:37,367 --> 00:45:42,539
This is a token that means
you can trust me no matter what.

580
00:46:32,556 --> 00:46:33,790
I had a feeling...

581
00:46:36,860 --> 00:46:38,996
that you were crying again.

582
00:46:42,432 --> 00:46:44,368
Final Episode
Special 15-minute Extension!

583
00:46:44,401 --> 00:46:47,004
I just want a normal average job.

584
00:46:47,037 --> 00:46:49,373
This job is about
letting people dream.

585
00:46:49,573 --> 00:46:51,375
I want you to keep smiling.

586
00:46:51,375 --> 00:46:53,277
This drama is fictional

587
00:46:53,277 --> 00:46:54,344
Nami!
